    <statement>
        <p>
       
        
                <p>
                    A driver's license starts with a special code(given by the letter A,B,C, or D), then has 6 digits(0 - 9), and ends with 4 letters. The letters can't repeat and the digits can't repeat.
                    <ol>
                        <li>Draw a diagram of the situation using boxes/slots.</li>
                        <li>How many driver's licenses can be created that fit this criteria?</li>
                    </ol>
                </p>         
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>[4][10][9][8][7][6][5][26][25][24][23]</li>
                <li>Multiplying all of the boxes together, there are 217002240000 total possibilities that fit the criteria.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
